Part II — The 9 Advanced Forms

These are your “black belt” moves.

⸻

13. Invert

Glyph: 1/x or ↺
Find the reverse operation, or ask what operation would undo the current one.

Use:
	•	debugging
	•	causality tracing
	•	“what created this pattern?”

Combat lesson:
Walk the footprint backward to the hidden gate.

⸻

14. Rescale

Glyph: ⇔scale
Change the size, timescale, or resolution.

Use:
	•	micro ↔ macro translation
	•	zooming between local and global behavior
	•	identifying scale-dominant laws

Combat lesson:
A jab at one scale is a campaign at another.

⸻

15. Threshold

Glyph: |
Identify the critical boundary where system behavior changes phase.

Use:
	•	tipping points
	•	activation energy
	•	failure boundaries
	•	Kairos windows

Combat lesson:
Do not waste force before the hinge. Strike at the hinge.

⸻

16. Weave

Glyph: #
Interlock multiple transformation chains into one mesh.

Use:
	•	narrative systems
	•	ecosystems
	•	institutions
	•	code architecture
	•	multi-layer causality

Combat lesson:
One thread breaks; a braid pulls ships.

⸻

17. Delay

Glyph: …
Treat waiting as an active transformation, not absence.

Use:
	•	option preservation
	•	signal clarification
	•	timing arbitrage
	•	emotional cooling

Combat lesson:
The unopened hand is still a move.

⸻

18. Null / Silence

Glyph: 0 or ∅
Introduce absence as a structural operator.

Use:
	•	contrast generation
	•	reset
	•	placeholders
	•	negative space
	•	informational gaps
	•	zero-state calibration

Combat lesson:
What you do not strike shapes the field of what can be struck.

⸻

19. Fuse Opposites

Glyph: ⊕
Hold two apparently contradictory views in a larger structure.

Use:
	•	wave/particle style dualities
	•	public/private truth
	•	compression/expressivity
	•	order/randomness edge states

Combat lesson:
Do not choose between the two blades until you know the hand that holds them.

⸻

20. Relay

Glyph: ≫
Pass a structure through multiple mirrors or domains in sequence.

Use:
	•	proof refinement
	•	cross-domain idea transfer
	•	design translation
	•	multi-model checking

Combat lesson:
One angle lies; three angles triangulate.

⸻

21. Canonize

Glyph: ★
Promote a discovered pattern to a reusable doctrine or library item.

Use:
	•	standardization
	•	toolkit building
	•	doctrine creation
	•	memory formation

Combat lesson:
Do not relearn the same strike every winter. Name it and keep it.

