Part III — The Transformation Tensor Array

Here is a compact way to store the whole library.

Tensor schema

Each move can be encoded as:

T = [Input_Form, Output_Form, Preserved, Changed, Cost, Risk, Scale, Reversible, Use_Mode]

Example:

Rotate

[frame_A, frame_B, invariant_structure, perspective, low, medium, all, yes, insight]

Compress

[rich_form, token, core_pattern, detail, low, high, all, partial, storage]

Threshold

[continuous_state, phase_state, governing_parameter, regime, medium, medium, scale-specific, maybe, timing]

