Part VII — A field example

Suppose the problem is:

“I have a powerful idea but it is messy and I can’t make it usable.”

Use the manual:
	1.	Split
Separate idea, emotion, strategy, jargon, implementation.
	2.	Filter
Keep the core invariant.
	3.	Compress
Name it in one sentence.
	4.	Lift
What class of thing is this really? Protocol? engine? doctrine? marketplace?
	5.	Project
Turn it into a checklist, diagram, module, or pitch.
	6.	Canonize
Add it to the library.

That is the martial version of thought.

